# CareerOS — Obey the Constitution

The binding rules are in `docs/engineering-constitution.md` and the five locked specs
(`docs/vision.md`, `docs/system-architecture.md`, `docs/domain-model.md`, `docs/ai-architecture.md`,
`docs/technical-architecture.md`). **Read them; do not restate or duplicate them here.**

## Non-negotiables (full list: Constitution §26)

- No business logic in UI, routers, or controllers.
- No LLM calls in React components or on the request path.
- No DB/LLM/vendor SDK calls outside `infrastructure`/adapters — everything external is behind a Port.
- No hardcoded prompts, model names, or secrets.
- No AI artifact leaving the platform (or representing the user) without human approval.
- No fabricated resume/profile content (grounding is mandatory, zero-fabrication is a hard gate).
- No cross-context access except via domain events or published contracts.
- No circular dependencies; no god classes/aggregates.

## Amendment rule

Any deviation from the Constitution or a locked document **requires an ADR** in `docs/adr/`,
merged **before** the deviating code. No ADR → no deviation. When unsure, stop and open an ADR.

## Before finishing

Meet the Definition of Done (Constitution §25) and the Code Review Checklist (§24).
